<p>The Maleceptor is a living vessel for the Hive Mind. Warp energy spears from its eyeless cranium to vaporise anything in its path, and those with minds strong enough to survive its keening psychic screams are laid low by its powerful talons. Even in defence the creature is a potent foe, for its sixfold mind-nodes generate a psychic barrier that consumes the bullets and energy blasts sent to slay it. These brain-arrays also fulfil another, more sinister role. The ethereal pseudopods that snake out from the Maleceptor’s glistening lobes are best described as the Shadow in the Warp made manifest. Should one of these ectoplasmic tendrils so much as brush against an enemy, the psychic immensity of the Hive Mind will invade the victim’s brain, overloading it with such catastrophic force that its head explodes.</p>